-4351-8b66-49f34ae1a0eb.jpg','Dengue IgG Capture ELISA',NULL,'In secondary infections, IgG response may rise quickly before or \r\nsimultaneously with an IgM response and will become the predominant immunoglobulin isotype in secondary infections.\r\n\r\nSuitable marker for secondary dengue infection\r\n\r\nHigh accuracy with all dengue serotypes(DEN1,2,3, and 4)\r\n\r\nSimple and easy to use: All necessary reagents included in the kit\r\n\r\nShelf life and storage temperature: 18 months from the date of manufacturing at 2-8 °C\r\n\r\nPerformance: Sensitivity 98.8 % / Specificity 99.2 %',NULL,'dengue-igg-capture-elisa',NULL,'USD',0.00,1,1,NULL,'','','<p>In primary infection with the dengue virus, IgG antibody appears a few days after IgM. IgG antibodies are produced at a lower level compared to IgM but will persist for many years after infection.</p>','','Dengue IgG Capture ELISA',''),(104,'users/images/f1c9fb88-ef7c-4784-afb8-2ca4422097dd.jpg','SD ELISA',NULL,'Early diagnosis of dengue infection (Especially in primary dengue infection)\r\n\r\nHigh accuracy with all dengue serotypes(DEN1,2,3, and 4)\r\n\r\nSimple and easy to use: All necessary reagents included in the kit\r\n\r\nShelf life and storage temperature: 18 months from the date of manufacturing at 2-8 °C\r\n\r\nIncluded in the WHO Bulk Procurement Scheme\r\n\r\nPerformance: Sensitivity 96.4 % / Specificity: 98.9 % (vs. HAI test)',NULL,'sd-elisa',NULL,'USD',0.00,1,1,NULL,'','','<p>In primary infection with the dengue virus, IgM antibody becomes detectable about five days after disease onset, when circulating virus declines in the blood. IgM level rises quickly to peak at about 2 weeks and declines to undetectable level after 2-3 months In secondary infections, IgM response is typically at a lower level compared to that in primary infection.</p>','','Dengue IgM Capture ELISA',''),(105,'users/images/c6bb039a-61be-4c70-a874-9a65c0455903.jpg','SD Elisa Dengue',NULL,'Perfect, early diagnosis of dengue infection\r\n\r\nHigh accuracy with all dengue serotypes(DEN1,2,3, and 4)\r\n\r\nSimple and easy to use: All necessary reagents included in the kit\r\n\r\nShelf life and storage temperature: 18 months from the date of manufacturing at 2-8 °C\r\n\r\nPerformance: Sensitivity 93.3 %(112/120) / Specificity 98.9 %(178/180)',NULL,'sd-elisa-dengue',NULL,'USD',0.00,1,1,NULL,'','','<p>The presence of circulating non-structural glycoprotein (NS1) indicates Viremia. If sufficient virus is present, NS1 can be detectable in a patient&rsquo;s blood from day 0 to day 5 following disease onset. The detection of NS1 antigen is therefore useful as a test of early acute infection.</p>','','Dengue NS1 Ag ELISA',''),(106,'users/images/86bbc437-b0b3-43e5-85b1-12cd8faef8dc.jpg','SD ELISA Chikungunya',NULL,'Simple and easy to use: All necessary reagents included in the kit\r\n\r\nShelf life and storage temperature: 12 months from the date of manufacture.\r\n\r\nPerformance: Sensitivity 93.6 % / Specificity 95.9 %',NULL,'sd-elisa-chikungunya',NULL,'USD',0.00,1,1,NULL,'','','<p>SD Chikungunya IgM ELISA is for the qualitative detection of IgM antibodies specific to Chikungunya in human serum. Useful to distinguish Chikungunya from dengue virus infection. To ensure analysis of larger quantities of specimens in the event of large outbreaks or serosurveys</p>','','Chikungunya IgM ELISA',''),(107,'users/images/97c668d8-d37c-4e37-b052-a973826d0488.jpg','SD Elisa Leptospira',NULL,'Efficient diagnosis of leptospirosis\r\n\r\nSimple and easy to use: All necessary reagents included in the kit\r\n\r\nShelf life and storage temperature: 12 months from the date of manufacturing at 2-8 °C\r\n\r\nPerformance: Sensitivity 97.2 % / Specificity 99.1 %',NULL,'sd-elisa-leptospira',NULL,'USD',0.00,1,1,NULL,'','','<p>SD Leptospira IgM ELISA is for the qualitative detection of IgM antibodies against leptospira antigen in human serum, as an aid in the clinical laboratory diagnosis of Leptospirosis.</p>','','Leptospira IgM ELISA',''),(108,'users/images/2b4c6bc9-049e-4107-8942-64bed4d30f2d.jpg','SD Elisa H.pylori',NULL,'Optimal choice to confirm treatment efficacy\r\n\r\nSuitable for mass screening test of H.pylori infection\r\n\r\nIndicator of active H. pylori infection\r\n\r\nSimple and easy to use: All necessary reagents included in the kit\r\n\r\nShelf life and storage temperature: 18 months from the date of manufacturing.\r\n\r\nPerformance: Sensitivity 100 % / Specificity 100 %',NULL,'sd-elisa-hpylori',NULL,'USD',0.00,1,1,NULL,'','','<p>SD H.pylori Ag ELISA is for the qualitative detection of Helicobacter pylori antigen in human fecal specimens, as an aid in the clinical laboratory diagnosis of H. pylori infection.</p>','','H.pylori Ag ELISA',''),(109,'users/images/97fba223-9b2c-41f7-96ab-5a8111bbfe43.jpg','UroColor',NULL,'Clear positive and negative results\r\n\r\nGood resistance to humidity\r\n\r\nChecking the interference in Glucose, Blood, Bilirubin, and \r\n\r\nNitrite by Vitamin C ingested\r\n\r\nNo color change after testing is completed\r\n\r\nNo color spread between pH and Specific gravity\r\n\r\nNo interference in protein by alkali urine\r\n\r\nShelf life: 24 months from the date of manufacturing\r\n\r\nDifferent color packages by parameters\r\n\r\nFast result visually or instrumentally',NULL,'urocolor',NULL,'USD',0.00,1,1,NULL,'','','<p>Test for Blood, Bilirubin, Urobilinogen, Ketone, Protein, Nitrite, Glucose, pH, Specific gravity, Leucocytes, and Ascorbic acid in urine.</p>','','Urine Chemistry Strip',''),(110,'users/images/31d3f636-3b66-413a-bf0f-d0f8cfcf3f80.jpg','SD UroMeter 120',NULL,'Auto calibration with power-on\r\n\r\nSimple and excellent compatibility by the USB communication port\r\n\r\nEnhancing user-convenience even for left-hander by ergonomics design\r\n\r\nEnhancing work efficiency by flexible options between quick mode & normal mode\r\n\r\nEasy to input multiple ID by the key board, PC and barcode reader\r\n\r\nApplicable to your multi-language by user define method',NULL,'sd-urometer-120',NULL,'USD',0.00,1,1,NULL,'','','<p>Take increased throughput and improved workflow together with precision.</p>','','Urine Chemistry Analyzer','');
